<p><strong><em>Disintegration.</em></strong> If the pentadrone dies, its body disintegrates into dust, leaving behind its weapons and anything else it was carrying.</p>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Multiattack.</em></strong> The pentadrone makes five arm attacks.</p>

<p><strong><em>Arm.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +4 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 5 (1d6 + 2) bludgeoning damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Paralysis Gas (Recharge 5-6).</em></strong> The pentadrone exhales a 30-foot cone of gas. Each creature in that area must succeed on a DC 11 Constitution saving throw or be paralyzed for 1 minute. A creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success.</p>

